The paper discusses feature extraction from persistence diagrams, which is a common topic in machine learning. The experiments conducted in the paper involve classification tasks related to manifold, human shapes, and protein classification, which are all relevant to computer vision and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to obtain adaptive template functions/features, which is related to data science (cs.DS) and neural networks (cs.NE).
